cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks related to pedestrian detection, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and Spatial Pyramid Pooling (SPP) layers also suggests that it may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories. Additionally, the paper deals with generating data in real scenes, which could potentially fall under the cs.GR (Graphics) category. Finally, the use of pedestrian detection models suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) category, as pedestrian detection is an important task in robotics applications such as autonomous vehicles.
